race.comment: BASSETT'S CHOICE (9) kept safe in betting on debut when she showed good early speed before fading late to run eighth over 1200m at Warwick Farm on April 16. Looks ready to go with the two forward trials and the cross-over nose band goes on. Hard to hold out. ROYAL AIR FORCE (4) closed strongly after pulling early and racing greenly in the straight with a respectable second over 1100m at this track first-up. Blinkers come off and the winkers go on. No excuses from the inside barrier. YOU SEXY THING (10) caught the eye first-up after going back from the sticky gate before launching late with a narrow fifth over 1250m here. Strips fitter and sure to be thereabouts. SNITZEL MISS (1) improving with racing and looks well placed with the in-form Siena Grima's 3kg claim. Likely to go back from the draw and launch late.
